<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1185,2041]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1438,1464]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Etymology</emphasis>
. From the Latin terms ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fullaway" authorityYear="1911" box="[594,655,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Callirhytis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[594,655,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ for black and ‘ 
<emphasis box="[831,879,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">crus</emphasis>
’ for leg, as this species has hindlegs (basal half of coxae, femorae, tibiae, basal and distal tarsomeres) almost totally black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1185,2041]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1509,1536]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species can be separated by the rest of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1840" box="[841,951,1511,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[841,951,1511,1537]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Ceroptres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having legs almost entirely black with testaceous joints. 
<taxonomicName box="[352,573,1547,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricrus">
<emphasis box="[352,573,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Ceroptres nigricrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobato-Vila &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2019" box="[976,1128,1547,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[976,995,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1010,1128,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which can be distinguished by the length of the radial cell (
<quantity box="[593,658,1582,1608]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.858" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="in" value="2.7">2.7 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[664,800,1583,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricrus">
<emphasis box="[664,800,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. nigricrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity box="[813,876,1582,1608]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.096" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="in" value="2.4">2.4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobato-Vila &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2019" box="[883,1033,1583,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[883,1033,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the length of the last flagellar segment (2.7 as wide as long in 
<taxonomicName box="[473,609,1619,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricrus">
<emphasis box="[473,609,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. nigricrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, about 4.0 in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobato-Vila &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2019" box="[762,913,1619,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[762,913,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the shape of female antennae (subclavate in 
<taxonomicName box="[181,318,1655,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricrus">
<emphasis box="[181,318,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. nigricrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, filiform in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobato-Vila &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2019" box="[457,609,1655,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[457,609,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), among others (see the descriptions of both species and the key to valid species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1840" box="[269,379,1691,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[269,379,1691,1717]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Ceroptres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
